ed as the state religion; the Chosŏn period (1392–1910), when Buddhism was actively suppressed by the Neo-Confucian Court; and the contemporary resurgence of female monasticism that began in the latter part of the twentieth century.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aBuddhist nunszKorea. 0aMonastic and religious life (Buddhism)zKorea. 0aMonastic and religious life of women. 4aAsian Studies : Asian Religion and Philosophy. 4aAsian Studies : Asian Studies. 4aAsian Studies : Korean Studies. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Buddhism. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Religion. 7aRELIGION / Buddhism / History.2bisacsh1 aBuswell, Robert E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCho, Eun-su, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCho, Eun-su, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHeo, Heung-sik, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJorgensen, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJung, Ji-Young, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKim, Young Mi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPark, Pori, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPuggioni, Tonino, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438435121423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438435121/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles